Coding Standards reference
Keeping the framework maintainable over time by establishing these rules from the outset:

One responsibility per module.
One technical check per script.
No hardcoded framework mappings in PowerShell.
All mappings stored in JSON.
Every check returns the standardized ComplianceFinding object.
Every function uses comment-based help and approved PowerShell verbs.
Every module includes Pester tests.
All output passes through the reporting engine; checks never write directly to Excel or the database.
Structured logging for all major operations.
Semantic versioning for releases.
